# Purpose

Step-by-step procedure for adding a new route to an existing backend module (e.g. `auth`, `jobs`).

# Workflow

## 1. Define the Route Constant

Add to `backend/src/shared/constants/routes/index.ts`:

```typescript
export const routes = {
  <module>: {
    // existing routes...
    <newAction>: '/<module>/<action>',
  },
};
```

## 2. Define Zod Schemas

In `backend/src/modules/<module>/schemas/`:
- Create `<action>-input.schema.ts` for request body.
- Create `<action>-response.schema.ts` for response shape (used by OpenAPI registry).
- Export from the module's `schemas/index.ts`.

## 3. Derive Types

In `backend/src/modules/<module>/types/`:

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';
import { <action>InputSchema } from '../schemas';

export type <Action>Input = z.infer<typeof <action>InputSchema>;
```

## 4. Write Input Validation Middleware

In `backend/src/modules/<module>/<module>-middleware.ts`:

```typescript
const validate<Action> = (req: Request, _res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
    const validated = validateRequestPayload(
        <action>InputSchema,
        req.body,
        ErrorMessage.<MODULE>_SCHEMA_VALIDATION_FAILED
    );
    req.body = validated;
    next();
};
```

## 5. Write Controller Handler

In `backend/src/modules/<module>/<module>-controller.ts`:

```typescript
const <action> = async (req: Request<Params, unknown, <Action>Input>, res: Response) => {
    // Use req.context.db.repository.<resource> for data access
    // Throw typed exceptions on error
    res.status(HttpStatusCode.<STATUS>).json({ success: true, data: result });
};
```

## 6. Wire the Route

In `backend/src/modules/<module>/<module>-routing.ts`:

```typescript
router.<method>(constants.routes.<module>.<newAction>, rateLimiter, validateUserInput, validate<Action>, <action>);
```

## 7. Register in OpenAPI

In `backend/src/modules/<module>/<module>-registry.ts`:

```typescript
registry.registerPath({
    method: '<method>',
    path: constants.routes.<module>.<newAction>,
    request: { body: { content: { 'application/json': { schema: <action>InputSchema } } } },
    responses: { 200: { ... } },
});
```

## 8. Regenerate Frontend Types

```bash
cd frontend && npm run generate-types
```

## Validation Commands

```bash
cd backend && npm run type-check && npm run lint
cd frontend && npm run type-check
cd backend && npm run test:integration
```

## Completion Criteria

- [ ] Route constant added to `shared/constants/routes`
- [ ] Zod schemas defined and exported
- [ ] Types derived from schemas (not manually written)
- [ ] Validation middleware written and wired
- [ ] Controller handler reads from `req.context`
- [ ] OpenAPI registry updated
- [ ] Frontend types regenerated
- [ ] Integration test added for the new endpoint
